@pcdavid - I added a workaround in SimRel so that I can proceed. See [this change to SimRel](https://git.eclipse.org/r/c/simrel/org.eclipse.simrel.build/+/189612/5/gmp-gmf-runtime.aggrcon). Summary is that [I made](https://git.eclipse.org/r/c/orbit/orbit-recipes/+/192337/2/releng/repository-simrel/gmf-runtime/pom.xml) a special [p2 site](https://download.eclipse.org/tools/orbit/downloads/drops-simrel/gmf-runtime/) that has only the missing dependencies of gmf-runtime and added that to the gmf-runtime contribution of simrel.

When this issue is resolved (i.e. you have a new version ready to publish) you can take the workaround out of your aggrcon file.

Please let me know if you have any questions.

This is really just a cosmetic issue, but now that the sources are on GitHub, the fact that all the features and plug-ins are top-level directories completely hides the README from the main repo page.

They could be reorganized into:
* `bundles` for the plug-ins / OSGi bundles;
* `features` for the features;
* `releng` for the top-level POM, the target platform definitions and the repository definition.

I encounter a ClassCastException in a diagram because my diagram is a `org.eclipse.ui.IWorkbenchPart` an not a `org.eclipse.gmf.runtime.diagram.ui.parts.IDiagramWorkbenchPart`. The following code is the main cause in `org.eclipse.gmf.runtime.diagram.ui.properties.sections.grid.RulerGridPropertySection.initWorkspacePropertyListener()`:
```java
	private void initWorkspacePropertyListener() {
		IDiagramWorkbenchPart editor = (IDiagramWorkbenchPart) getPart();
		if (editor == null) return;
		DiagramGraphicalViewer viewer = (DiagramGraphicalViewer) editor.getDiagramGraphicalViewer();
		workspaceViewerProperties = viewer.getWorkspaceViewerPreferenceStore();
		workspaceViewerProperties.addPropertyChangeListener(propertyListener);
	}
```
We should check the type of  `getPart()`. Here is a hot fix that can be proposed in the next PR (PR #25):
```java
	private void initWorkspacePropertyListener() {
		IWorkbenchPart activePart = getPart();
		IDiagramWorkbenchPart editor = null;
		if (activePart instanceof IDiagramWorkbenchPart) {
			editor = (IDiagramWorkbenchPart) activePart;
		} else {
			editor = activePart.getAdapter(IDiagramWorkbenchPart.class);
		}
		if (editor == null)
			return;
		DiagramGraphicalViewer viewer = (DiagramGraphicalViewer) editor.getDiagramGraphicalViewer();
		workspaceViewerProperties = viewer.getWorkspaceViewerPreferenceStore();
		workspaceViewerProperties.addPropertyChangeListener(propertyListener);
	}
```
